						               													<description>Cube Words is a print&amp;amp;play word game for 2 players. Earn points by forming words using adjacent letters. First player to earn exactly 30 points is the winner.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;In his turn, each player can form a 3+ letters word using orthogonally adjacent letters and earn points according to the number of letters. Longer words are considerably more valuable than short words.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;After forming a word, each player can use a cube to block a chosen letter. This letter can not be used by the other player.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Each player can only pass through the 20 points mark if he has formad at least one 6+ letters word.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;To make things a little more difficult, the winner is the player who reachs exactly 30 points. If you earn more than 30 points, you begin to reduce your scoring!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The game was designed for the 2017 9-Card Nanogame P&amp;amp;P Design Contest.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;THE COMPONENTS&amp;#10;&amp;#10;All you need to play Cube Words is:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;- The cards fronts and backs (one A4 sheet for each)&amp;#10;- 8 cubes, in 2 different colors (4 for each player)&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
